East Tulare Village first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that East Tulare Villa had a population of 773. The population density was {{convert|2,741.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of East Tulare Villa was 303 (39.2%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 28 (3.6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 9 (1.2%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.1%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 294 (38.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 138 (17.9%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 491 persons (63.5%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=East Tulare Villa CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0621210 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 5, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 214 households, out of which 120 (56.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 128 (59.8%) were married-couple households, 12 (5.6%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 43 (20.1%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 31 (14.5%) had a male householder with no partner present. 18 households (8.4%) were one person, and 9 (4.2%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.61.<ref name=DP1/> There were 192 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (89.7% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=East Tulare Villa CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0621210 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 5, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 246 people (31.8%) under the age of 18, 76 people (9.8%) aged 18 to 24, 201 people (26.0%) aged 25 to 44, 152 people (19.7%) aged 45 to 64, and 98 people (12.7%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 30.6{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 102.4 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 222 housing units at an average density of {{convert|787.2|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 214 (96.4%) were occupied. Of these, 131 (61.2%) were owner-occupied, and 83 (38.8%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

